220|// Brazil (America/Sao_Paulo) is a fixed UTC-3 — no DST since 2019. Order
221|// timestamps are stored in UTC, but the dashboard's calendar day must follow
222|// the store's LOCAL (BRT) day. Otherwise late-night BRT orders, which fall on
223|// the next UTC day, are bucketed into the wrong day's GMV (a 21:39 BRT sale on
224|// the 15th showed up under the 16th). Traffic DailyMetric rows are date-keyed
225|// in the provider's own day and are intentionally NOT shifted here.
226|const BRT_OFFSET_MS = 3 * 60 * 60 * 1000;
